article.headline: UCF 81, FLA Inst Tech 37
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Jermaine Taylor scored 15 points to lead Central Florida to a 81-37 win over Florida Tech Friday. Josh Peppers put up another 12 points for Central Florida (4-0), along with 11 from Mike Battle. All 12 Golden Knights that played scored at least three points each. Central Florida took a 23-5 lead early in the first half. The team's defense managed to hold Florida Tech (1-3) to just one field goal in the first 10:48 of play. After taking a 35-12 lead into the break Central Florida went on to finish the game shooting 28-for-56 from the field. The high scorer for Florida Tech was Sean Zeller with nine points, all from 3-point range.
